<FONT FACE="AGaramond" SIZE=4><B>Instructor:  </B> <A HREF="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~kay">David G. Kay</A>,
406B Computer Science. Office hours: Officially Wednesdays after class,
but feel free to drop by any time or send electronic mail to </FONT><FONT FACE="Courier" SIZE=4><TT><A HREF="mailto:kay@ics.uci.edu">kay</A></TT></FONT><FONT FACE="AGaramond" SIZE=4>.<A NAME="_14_233"></A>
<BR>
<B>Meeting place and times:  </B>Wednesdays from 9:00 to 11:50, in IERF
B011.
<BR>
<B>Course requirements:</B>  Reading and attending class to discuss the
course materials; a term project on a computer law topic of your choice,
presented orally (half talk, half discussion); one take-home final exam
(out at the end of the ninth week, due at the start of finals week).
<BR>
<B><A HREF="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~kay/courses/264/s05readings.html">Readings:</A></B>
 I&#39;ll assign readings as we go.  Some will be on-line; others will be
available in the ICS grad course handout file, in the filing cabinet outside
the ICS kitchen.  The course home page is <A NAME="_14_784"></A></FONT><FONT FACE="Courier New"><A HREF="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~kay/courses/264/">http://www.ics.uci.edu/~kay/courses/264/</A><A NAME="_14_827"></A></FONT><FONT FACE="AGaramond" SIZE=4>.
 The course Email list is <A NAME="_14_858"></A></FONT><FONT FACE="Courier New"><A HREF="mailto:37110-s05@classes.uci.edu">37110-s05@classes.uci.edu</A></FONT><FONT FACE="AGaramond" SIZE=4>;
feel free to post questions or comments.
